title: Austria Private Debt to GDP
description: Private Debt to GDP in Austria decreased to 173.80 percent in 2021 from 174.30 percent in 2020. Private Debt to GDP in Austria averaged 153.59 percent from 1995 until 2021, reaching an all time high of 174.30 percent in 2020 and a record low of 123.70 percent in 1995. Private sector debt to GDP measures the indebtedness of both sectors, non-financial corporations and households and non-profit institutions serving households, as a percentage of GDP.
author: OECD
